            <section>
               <id root="9790e65d-5ca6-4c30-b863-771629c43fa4"/>
               <code code="51945-4" codeSystem="2.16.840.1.113883.6.1" displayName="PACKAGE LABEL.PRINCIPAL DISPLAY PANEL"/>
               <text>
                  <paragraph>NITROGEN</paragraph>
                  <paragraph/>
                  <paragraph>REFRIGERATED LIQUID NF</paragraph>
                  <paragraph>
                     <br/>
                  </paragraph>
                  <paragraph>UN1977</paragraph>
                  <paragraph/>
                  <paragraph>REFRIGERATED LIQUID</paragraph>
                  <paragraph>ALWAYS KEEP CONTAINER IN UPRIGHT POSITION.</paragraph>
                  <paragraph>DO NOT CHANGE OR FORCE FIT CONNECTIONS.</paragraph>
                  <paragraph>Rx ONLY.</paragraph>
                  <br/>
                  <paragraph/>
                  <paragraph>WARNING:<content>         </content>Administration
of Nitrogen may be hazardous or contraindicated.<content>  </content>For use only by or under the supervision of a
licensed practitioner who is experienced in the use and administration of
Nitrogen and is familiar with the indications, effects, dosages, methods, and
frequency and duration of administration, and with the hazards,
contraindications and side effects and the precautions to be taken.</paragraph>
                  <paragraph/>
                  <paragraph>WARNING:<content>         </content>EXTREMELY
COLD LIQUID AND GAS UNDER PRESSURE.<content>  </content>CAN
CAUSE RAPID SUFFOCATION.<content>  </content>CAN CAUSE
SEVERE FROSTBITE.</paragraph>
                  <paragraph>
                     <br/>
                  </paragraph>
                  <paragraph/>
                  <paragraph>Store and use with adequate ventilation.</paragraph>
                  <paragraph>Do not get liquid in eyes, on skin or clothing.</paragraph>
                  <paragraph>For liquid withdrawal, wear face shield and gloves.</paragraph>
                  <paragraph>Do not drop.<content>  </content>Use
suitable hand truck for container movement.</paragraph>
                  <paragraph>Cylinder temperature should not exceed 52C (125F).</paragraph>
                  <paragraph>Close valve after each use and when empty.</paragraph>
                  <paragraph>Use a back flow Preventive device in the piping.</paragraph>
                  <paragraph>Use in accordance with the MATERIAL SAFETY DATA SHEET
(MSDS).</paragraph>
                  <br/>
                  <paragraph/>
                  <paragraph>FIRST AID:</paragraph>
                  <paragraph>IF INHALED, remove to fresh air.<content>  </content>If not breathing, give artificial respiration.<content>  </content>If breathing is difficult, give oxygen.<content>  </content>Call a physician.</paragraph>
                  <paragraph>IN CASE OF FROSTBITE, obtain medical treatment
immediately.</paragraph>
                  <br/>
                  <paragraph/>
                  <paragraph>DO NOT REMOVE THIS PRODUCT LABEL.</paragraph>
                  <br/>
                  <paragraph>AMERICAN WELDING AND GAS</paragraph>
                  <paragraph>5600 PACKER DRIVE</paragraph>
                  <paragraph>WAUSAU, WI 54401</paragraph>
                  <paragraph>
                     <renderMultiMedia referencedObject="MM3"/>
                  </paragraph>
                  <br/>
               </text>
